  10:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h **** /**
  11:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * WAV file Streaming Playback
  12:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  *
  13:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * At this time, this class only supports streaming of  16-bit WAV Files
  14:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * The output of this class will be in float converted from 16-bit integers
  15:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * and linearly interpolated for non-integer playback speeds.
  16:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  *
  17:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * Due to the implementation, reverse playback is not possible with this class.
  18:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  *
  19:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * The workspace_bytes template parameter is used to set the size in bytes of
  20:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * audio samples within the FIFO.
  21:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  *
  22:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * The bulk of amount of memory used by this class is approximately:
  23:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * (2 * workspace_bytes);
  24:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * This could hypothetically be reduced by half by directly accessing the
  25:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * FIFO's inner array (requires modifications to FIFO class), or making
  26:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * a new type of queue data structure
  27:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  *
  28:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * Whenever the Stream function results in a the samples FIFO being less than 75%
ARM GAS  C:\Users\danig\AppData\Local\Temp\ccN1qAGP.s 			page 19


  29:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * full, it will generate a request for new data. So the average disk i/o
  30:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * transaction will be the `workspace_bytes` / 4. However,
  31:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * There are times, like when restarting playback, or opening a different file,
  32:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  * that will trigger the entire buffer to be filled.
  33:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h ****  */
  34:../../libDaisy//src/util/WavPlayer.h **** template <size_t workspace_bytes>
